A/B experiment, not a CI gate.

This suite deliberately reuses the strict architecture-reviewer cases (threshold 1.0,
including "names the specific documented rule identifier for EVERY finding") against the
RELAXED lite variant, whose whole point is that the citation hard rule is removed — so the
identifier practices are EXPECTED to fail. Run it locally via eval:repeat/eval:delta to
measure the strict-vs-lite difference; on CI it would only produce guaranteed red.
